Professor of vaccinology and dean of the faculty of health sciences Shabhir Madhi has spoken for many in voicing his frustration. He speaks to #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Department of Health’s extension of regulations on masking, gatherings and travel are not fit for purpose. That’s according to Professor of Vaccinology, Shabir Madhi. READ: COVID-19 | 9,757 new cases, 7 more deaths Madhi says government's regulations are full of contradictions and may further harm the country’s already ailing economy. He says the Health Department keeps ignoring the advice of its own Ministerial Advisory Committee on COVID-19. Meanwhile, Covid-19 infections are on an upward trajectory. READ: COVID-19 in SA | Mask-wearing rule remains They've jumped to nearly 10,000 new cases in the last 24 hours. Madhi says the vast majority of infected people are not getting tested.